I once had a guy in my life who wouldn’t let me eat. I would order food and he would send it back when it came saying “we didn’t order that” when he knew damn well I did. I would go to the restroom and he would have the waiter take my plate when I was away. I would get death glares if I ever happened to finish my meal. Dessert and apps were obviously forbidden. Long story short we didn’t last very long. I still think of you every time a real man lets me eat whatever I want. For the full story go to my sunroom for my vlog diary☀️
All I want from you is your attention.

I stand strong with my fellow SAG members during this tough time of fighting for what is right, now more than ever we need to uplift and support our fellow unions! I was so honored to attend Christopher Nolan’s screening in support of the hard work the entire crew put into making this film a reality. Some of the unions belief is to boycott the movies until matters are resolved and another part of the union thinks it’s important to see the movies that are done to prove to the studios they do need us. We’re in delicate times indeed but all the hard work the unions have already done shouldn’t go unnoticed. 💜💜💜
